<collectingRegion box="[529,712,302,329]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Hunan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[723,794,302,328]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">China</collectingCountry>
. On the website of Chinese Field Herbarium (https://www. cfh.ac.cn/album/ShowPhoto.aspx?photoid=55ab405d-bbb9-430b-952e-1fb4e3990e2e), we also found a similar plant from Hefeng county, 
<collectingRegion box="[374,551,374,400]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Hubei Province</collectingRegion>
. These two localities are very close to each other. It is reasonable to infer that the population of Hefeng is most likely to belong to the same species as Hupingshan specimen. It occurs on the roadside at altitudes of about 
<specimenCount box="[365,443,446,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="generic">
<quantity box="[365,439,446,473]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" unit="m" value="350.0">350 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,315,482,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Discussion</emphasis>
:—Because its phyllaries lack marginal spinules, wings, and scarious appendage and leaves abaxially lack spinules, the new species should belong to 
<emphasis box="[694,720,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">C.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[790,880,519,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[790,880,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Cirsium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[897,1182,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hupingshanicum">
<emphasis box="[897,1182,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Cirsium hupingshanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mostly similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">C. japonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[311,495,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<taxonomicName box="[311,491,554,581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemiforme">C. racemiforme</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The comparison of morphological characters between these three species are shown in 
<tableCitation box="[164,248,590,616]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,160,184]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of morphological characters of Cirsium hupingshanicum, C. japonicum and C. racemiforme." pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
